# Reflection

## What I Learned

Instruction-following evaluation requires checking every constraint individually rather than judging the response based only on overall quality. A response may be factually correct but still fail because it ignores explicit user instructions.

---

## What I'd Do Differently

Create a checklist before evaluating future responses to ensure no instruction is overlooked, especially measurable constraints like word count, formatting, and prohibited content.

